===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# [[at|At]] [[no]] [[time]]; on no [[occasion]]; in no [[circumstance]].
#* '''1634''', {{w||William Shakespeare}}, {{w|John Fletcher}}, ''[[s:The Two Noble Kinsmen/Act 2/Scene 4|The Two Noble Kinsmen]]'', Act 2, Scene 4,
#*: Why should I love this Gentleman? Tis odds / He '''never''' will affect me;
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1898|author={{w|Winston Churchill (novelist)|Winston Churchill}}
|title={{w|The Celebrity}}|chapter=1
|passage=In the old days, to my commonplace and unobserving mind, he gave no evidences of genius whatsoever. He '''never''' read me any of his manuscripts,&nbsp;[&hellip;], and therefore my lack of detection of his promise may in some degree be pardoned.}}
#* '''1908''', {{w|Lucy Maud Montgomery}}, ''[[s:Anne of Green Gables/Chapter XXI|Anne of Green Gables]]'', Chapter XXI: A New Departure in Flavorings,
#*: "I '''never''' thought you were so fond of Mr. Phillips that you'd require two handkerchiefs to dry your tears just because he was going away," said Marilla.
#* '''1919''', B. G. Jefferis, J. L. Nichols, ''[[s:Searchlights on Health/Sensible Rules for the Nurse|Searchlights on Health: Sensible Rules for the Nurse]]'',
#*: '''Never''' speak of the symptoms of your patient in his presence, unless questioned by the doctor, whose orders you are always to obey ''implicitly''.
#: {{ux|en|I finally finished, and I '''never''' want to do that again.}}
#: {{ux|en|I repeated the test a hundred times, and '''never''' saw a positive result.}}
#: {{ux|en|I will '''never''' tell.}}
# Not at any [[other]] time; not on any other occasion; not [[previously]].
#* '''1601''' November 30, {{w|Elizabeth I of England}}, ''[[s:Elizabeth I's Farewell Speech|Elizabeth I's Farewell Speech]]'',
#*: There is no jewel, be it of '''never''' so rich a price, which I set before this jewel: I mean your love.
#* '''1813''', {{w|Jane Austen}}, ''[[s:Pride and Prejudice/Chapter 4|Pride and Prejudice]]'', Chapter 4,
#*: "He is just what a young man ought to be," said she, "sensible, good-humoured, lively; and I '''never''' saw such happy manners!--so much ease, with such perfect good breeding!"
#* '''1908''', {{w|Lucy Maud Montgomery}}, ''[[s:Anne of Green Gables/Chapter XIII|Anne of Green Gables]]'', Chapter XIII: The Delights of Anticipation,
#*: I '''never''' saw such an infatuated man.
# {{lb|en|colloquial}} Negative particle (''used to negate verbs in the simple past tense; also used [[absolutely]]'').
#: {{ux|en|The police say I stole the car, but I '''never''' did it.}}
#: {{ux|en|You said you were going to mow the lawn today. – I '''never'''!}}<!--example of "never" used absolutely in this sense-->

